article.headline: Colorado St. 92, N. Colorado 78
article.story: GREELEY, Colo. -- Dorian Green scored a career high 36 points in leading Colorado State to its first road win, beating Northern Colorado 92-78 on Thursday night. Green was 8 for 10 on 3-pointers and had two, four-point plays for Colorado State (7-4). Green's previous career-best was 21 points. Wes Eikmeier added 15 with three treys of his own. The Rams made a season high 13 3-pointers and shot 54 percent from beyond the arc. Tate Unruh led Northern Colorado (3-8) with 15 points, but he went nearly 24 minutes without scoring. The Bears turned the ball 16 times and allowed 24 points off turnovers.
